        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><date>Thursday, 10th Nissan, 1865</date>.</p>
            <p>My friend and companion:</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">In view of your usual punctuality, I am somewhat<lb/> concerned
                because of your failure to reply to me or to send me the “Occident”<lb/> I beg for a
                few words by return mail.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Holzman</persName> is making collections from door to
                door,<lb/> in order to publish a pamphlet which he named, “<sic>EMek</sic> Rephaim”
                (Valley of<lb/> Ghosts), and which is directed against <persName>Wise</persName> and
                his cronies. He has<lb/> authorization for this from such Gaonim as
                    <persName>Raphall</persName>, who is gone and de-<lb/>parted from his world, and
                    <persName>Isaacs</persName>
                <add>whom he calls the heads of the people.</add>
                <persName>Wise</persName> and the others will be<lb/> delighted that orthodoxy has
                only such representatives who have taken<lb/> the lead. The thing is full of
                mistakes, insults, accusations, and con-<lb/>fusion. Such things cause me pain,
                “Those that destroy you and lay you<lb/> waste, come forth from yourself”. I have
                briefly disposed of <persName>Wise</persName> in<lb/> the —. It is me whom he means
                by “The sages of <placeName>New York</placeName>”. Unfortu-<lb/>nately I am not
                quite well and therefore must close.</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Yours sincerely,</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">Jonah Bondi</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="Envelope"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
